class PostRequestHandler(http.server.BaseHTTPRequestHandler):
            content_length = int(self.headers.get('Content-Length', 0))
            if content_length == 0:
                self.send_response(400)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "No data received"}).encode())
                return
            if self.headers.get('Content-Type') != 'application/json':
                self.send_response(400)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "Content-Type header is not application/json"}).encode())
                return
            data = self.rfile.read(content_length)
            try:
                json_data = json.loads(data)
                if 'data' not in json_data:
                    self.send_response(400)
                    self.end_headers()
                    self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "No data received"}).encode())
                    return
                self.send_response(200)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "success", "message": "Data received successfully."}).encode())
            except json.JSONDecodeError:
                self.send_response(400)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "Invalid JSON format"}).encode())

class PostRequestHandler(http.server.BaseHTTPRequestHandler):
            content_length = int(self.headers.get('Content-Length', 0))
            if content_length == 0:
                self.send_response(400)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "No data received"}).encode())
                return
            if self.headers.get('Content-Type') != 'application/json':
                self.send_response(400)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "Content-Type header is not application/json"}).encode())
                return
            data = self.rfile.read(content_length)
            try:
                json_data = json.loads(data)
                if 'data' not in json_data:
                    self.send_response(400)
                    self.end_headers()
                    self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "No data received"}).encode())
                    return
                self.send_response(200)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "success", "message": "Data received successfully."}).encode())
            except json.JSONDecodeError:
                self.send_response(400)
                self.end_headers()
                self.wfile.write(json.dumps({"status": "error", "message": "Invalid JSON format"}).encode())
